Explore Predictions and Improvements

In Einstein Discovery, a prediction is a probabilistic value of a future outcome, as calculated by a predictive model. Predictions are similar to the kind of regression or machine-learning analysis that data scientists conduct using advanced analytics tools.

To simulate and explore future outcomes:

Open a Model.
Click Predictions (1).
Select an option from one or more features.

Einstein Prediction: prediction score for your selections
Top Improvements: suggested actions to improve predicted outcome
Model Overview: metrics describing the quality of the model
Top Prediction Factors: explanatory variables most strongly associated with the predicted outcome
Insights: any insights associated with your prediction

To see recommendations for a given feature, select Actionable. If there are ways to statistically improve the predicted outcome, Einstein displays them in Top Improvements.
